<topic id="dc44c3a5-8545-4253-9da1-62258a00607c" revisionNumber="1">
    <developerConceptualDocument xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

        <introduction>
            <mediaLink>
                <image xlink:href="LogoBase"/>
            </mediaLink>
            <para>
                The DigitalRise Base library (<application>DigitalRise.dll</application>) is a .NET helper library containing
                functionality that is used in most DigitalRise libraries and applications.
            </para>
            <autoOutline/>
        </introduction>


        <section address="Features">
            <title>Features</title>
            <content>
                <para>
                    Here is an overview of features in this library:
                </para>
                <list class="bullet">
                    <listItem>
                        <link xlink:href="09d39ddf-c826-4943-aac8-2ef9e16e5a12" />
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <link xlink:href="9e2a4144-69e9-4bf2-8cea-79713eb91490"/>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <link xlink:href="ce7bca46-717a-4dfb-a154-acb6ee1e8ad9"/>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <link xlink:href="6736e3bc-383c-4d80-a828-c83fea5c3461" />
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Robust floating-point comparison (see class
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Mathematics.Numeric</codeEntityReference>)
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        New types of collections (see namespace
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Collections</codeEntityReference>)
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        New extension methods for LINQ (see namespace
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Linq</codeEntityReference>)
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Base implementation of the <legacyItalic>Singleton</legacyItalic> design pattern (see class
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Singleton`1</codeEntityReference>)
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Base implementation of an <legacyItalic>Undo/Redo</legacyItalic> framework (see
                        namespace <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Undo</codeEntityReference>)
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <link xlink:href="120bed13-f23b-4774-bae7-d64d410d2122">
                            Storage API for cross-platform file access and virtual file systems
                        </link>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Weak delegates and events
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        And more...
                    </listItem>
                </list>
            </content>
        </section>


        <section address="Namespaces">
            <title>Namespaces</title>
            <content>
                <para>
                    Following namespaces belong to the DigitalRise Base library:
                </para>
                <list class="nobullet">
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Animation</codeEntityReference>
                        <superscript>1</superscript>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Collections</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Diagnostics</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Linq</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Mathematics</codeEntityReference>
                        <superscript>2</superscript>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.ServiceLocation</codeEntityReference>
                        <superscript>3</superscript>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Storages</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Text</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Threading</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">N:DigitalRise.Undo</codeEntityReference>
                    </listItem>
                </list>
                <para>
                    <superscript>1</superscript> The DigitalRise Base library (<localUri>DigitalRise.dll</localUri>)
                    includes only the interfaces
                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Animation.IAnimatableObject</codeEntityReference>,
                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Animation.IAnimatableProperty</codeEntityReference>,
                    and <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Animation.IAnimatableProperty`1</codeEntityReference>.
                    All other types related to animation are defined in the DigitalRise Animation library
                    (<localUri>DigitalRise.Animation.dll</localUri>).
                </para>
                <para>
                    <superscript>2</superscript> The DigitalRise Base library (<localUri>DigitalRise.dll</localUri>)
                    includes only the type <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Mathematics.Numeric</codeEntityReference>.
                    All other types related to mathematics are defined in the DigitalRise Mathematics library
                    (<localUri>DigitalRise.Mathematics.dll</localUri>).
                </para>
                <para>
                    <superscript>3</superscript> The <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.ServiceLocation.ServiceContainer</codeEntityReference>
                    is available in a separate assembly (<localUri>DigitalRise.ServiceLocation.dll</localUri>) because
                    it requires a reference to a third-party assembly (<localUri>Microsoft.Practices.ServiceLocation.dll</localUri>).
                </para>
            </content>
        </section>


